column5: Kempenfelt Bay now has ice as far as I can see from the bottom. Nowhere near good ice yet, but it's a start. The snow in the forecast is not going to help things though.

I just want to be able to hop on the skidoo and go anywhere, do you think I can do that this weekend with Kempenfelt frozen and I wonder what Kempenfelt Kelly does in the winter  so many questions, so few answers..LOL
Yeah theres report thats theres 2"-3" at minets.Buddies son is running the rental there now,not Cannings. I dought he has the the right insurance if any, to operate this.
Do they catch much outta those huts??
The last couple of days I've seen a guy ice fishing out near Centennial Beach a few hundred feet out from shore. I think there's a wreck down there?
Gotz to be old George.Crazy bugger he is.First on and last one off.
I saw him too..  Ya, there's an old wooden wreck down there.
I would agree with the "crazy" assessment. There's only been ice there a few days, and in some areas not far from where he is it still looks wet!
That would be the warm water out flush,,,I mean flow.
You had to go and say that didint ya,,,,,,,,,,
...watch out for the dreaded "brown trout" you mean?
